value.value: Tooth row that is the mediodorsal row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone, located between the dorsal tooth row and ventral tooth row.
Tooth row that is the dorsalmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1MD and anterior to tooth 3MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2MD and anterior to tooth 4MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.
Placode that develops into a tooth. The placode is a thickening of the pharyngeal epithelium.

A migrating group of cells originating from the posterior lateral line placode.  The primordium deposits seven to nine neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its posterior migration to the tail. Gompel et al, 2001.
Scute that is a bony plate that forms in dorsal midline of body margin between the skull and dorsal fin.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to the neurocranium.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 1.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 2.
Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.
Endochondral bone and Weberian ossicle that is an element of the fourth vertebra that curves ventrally around the anterior head of the swim bladder.
Cartilaginous larval structure dorsal to the four anterior-most vertebrae, which forms the connection between neural arches and supraneurals in the Weberian apparatus. Bird and Mabee, 2003.
Epithelium lining the pharynx consisting largely of simple columnar epithelium with a short segment (1mm) of stratified squamous epithelium on the ventral side. Chen et al, 2007.

The outermost epidermal layer covering the fish at embryonic stages; derived from the EVL and thought to eventually be replaced by the superficial stratum of the epidermis. Sometimes used synonymously with EVL. Le Guellec et al, 2004.
Anatomical cluster that consists of the anteriormost vertebrae and associated structures that connect the swim bladder to the inner ear.

definition.value: Vertebra 1-4, and sometimes vertebra 5 in some catfishes, are part of the Weberian apparatus. Weberian apparatus is present in Otophysi.

value.value: Endochondral bone that forms around the notochord and is part of the vertebral column.
Vertebra that is part of the Weberian apparatus.

definition.value: Weberian vertebra are usually vertebra 1-4. Present in Otophysi.

value.value: Supraneural bone located dorsal to vertebra 2.

definition.value: In otophysans, supraneural 2 bone is part of the neural complex.

value.value: Supraneural bone that is located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

definition.value: In otophysans, supraneural 3 bone is part of the neural complex and fuses in development with neural arches 3 and 4.

value.value: Neural crest that is part of the head.

Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is the cartilaginous embryonic component of the lower jaw, or ventral mandibular arch. It develops into the endochondral articular and retroarticular bones. Meckel's cartilage is paired.
Anatomical cluster that is part of the cranium and consists of the jaws, hyoid and branchial arches.
Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with more than one pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.
Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with pharyngeal arches 3-5.
Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arches 4 and 5 (pharyngeal arches 6-7).
